2 imprisonment as provided for in subsections B through F of Section
3 20N of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes and a fine not more than
4 Twenty Thousand Dollars ($20,000.00), which shall be in addition to
5 other punishment provided by law and shall not be imposed in lieu of
6 other punishment. A second conviction for the violation of the
7 provisions of this paragraph is a Class D1 felony offense punishable
8 by a term of imprisonment as provided for in subsections B through F
